---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Logistical Mission Strategy Generator - In collaboration with Fleets-Online B.V. (https://fleets-online.com/)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Description:
This Knowledge-Based Engineering application can be used to generate the best strategy for logistical problems
in for example the agricultural, construction and transportation industries. The application uses fleet data
provided by the user and iterates over possible strategies to come up with a winning strategy, based on a weighted function
concerning one or more of the following goals: Time, Cost and/or Emissions (CO2 + NOx),
including the possibility of strict deadlines.
-------------------------
Usage:
To run the application, one should first specify its fleet, depot, and work site location in JSON format.
After that, the user should run the file 'main.py'. This file will instantiate the root object, called 'MissionStrategyApp'.
A ParaPy GUI will open, and the user can already look at a fleet visualisation on a map by pressing on 'root'
on the upper left corner of the screen. The user should specify its mission preferences, needed machinery,
amount of total man-hours corresponding to that needed machinery right below 'inputs on the bottom left of the GUI'.
In case there are strict deadlines (by pressing the check-box), the user should include the start time and deadline time.
After that, to that which contains buttons to run the mission generator, visualize different outputs and alter the used data.
-------------------------
Dependencies:
---
APIs
The FleetsOnline API is used by sending requests to 'https://api.v2.deepdigital.org', which requires a FleetsOnline
account for authentication. The credentials should be placed in the file 'EmissionsExternalTool.py'.
The OpenRouteService API is used, which requires an ORS account for authentication. The key should be placed in the
file 'Routing.py'.
---
Libraries
parapy v1.15.1
kbeutils v1.0
routingpy v1.3.1
numpy v2.4.6
requests v2.34.2
reportlab v4.5.1
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

================================================================================
LOGISTICAL MISSION STRATEGY GENERATOR
In collaboration with Fleets-Online B.V. (https://fleets-online.com/)
================================================================================

DESCRIPTION
-----------
This Knowledge-Based Engineering (KBE) application generates deterministic,
optimized logistical strategies for the agricultural, construction, and heavy
transportation industries. By instantiating parametric fleet data and
evaluating spatial-temporal constraints, the application iterates over
feasible transport missions to compute a winning strategy. Optimization is
driven by a multi-objective scalar cost function balancing:

  * Financial Cost (EUR)
  * Environmental Emissions (CO2 and NOx)
  * Operational Time (Hours)
  * Strict Temporal Deadlines

DEPENDENCIES & PREREQUISITES
----------------------------
1. External APIs
The application relies on two external web services for routing and emission
calculations. Users must possess valid authentication credentials for both:

  * FleetsOnline API: Used for dynamic CO2 and NOx calculations. Requests
    are routed to https://api.v2.deepdigital.org. Requires an active
    FleetsOnline account.
  * OpenRouteService (ORS) API: Used for geographic routing and distance
    matrices. Requires an active ORS account and API key.

2. Python Environment
The system is built on the ParaPy framework. Ensure your environment matches
the following specific library versions:
  * parapy == 1.15.1
  * kbeutils == 1.0
  * routingpy == 1.3.1
  * numpy == 2.4.6
  * requests == 2.34.2
  * reportlab == 4.5.1

USAGE & EXECUTION
-----------------
1. Data Initialization
Before executing the application, initialize the infrastructure and fleet
inventory. Specify the available machinery, depot locations, and worksite
boundaries in JSON format (CustomData.json or FleetsOnlineData.json).

2. Launching the Application
Execute the main script via your command line to instantiate the
MissionStrategyApp root object and launch the ParaPy Graphical User Interface (GUI):

    python main.py

3. User Interface Interaction
  * Initial Visualization: In the ParaPy GUI, click on the "root" node in
    the upper left tree. This immediately renders a map visualization of the
    initial spatial distribution of your fleet and depots. Machines that are
    very close to each other are vertically stacked for visual purposes.
  * Define Parameters: In the property window (bottom left), input your
    specific mission constraints:
      - Preferences: Weights for Cost, Emissions, and Time.
      - Requirements: The needed machinery type and the total required
        man-hours for the job.
      - Deadlines: If temporal constraints apply, check the strict deadline
        box and input the exact start and deadline times.
  * Execute & Visualize: Navigate to the actions panel. Use the provided
    'Generate Strategy' button to run the mission iterator, which calculates
    the winning strategy. Dynamically visualize the various outputs or
    alter the dataset.


OUTPUTS & DELIVERABLES
----------------------
Upon generating a winning strategy, the system provides several outputs
directly through the GUI actions panel:

  * Interactive Mapping: Visualizes the specific transport routes of the
    winning strategy.
  * Trailer Arrangements: Opens a 3D visualization of the algorithmic
    trailer packing.
  * Geometry Export: Exports the 3D arrangements of depots or loaded
    trailers as .stp files.
  * Strategy Report: Generates a comprehensive PDF detailing the normalized
    metrics and timeline of the selected logistical mission.

================================================================================